        "content": "<p>Neste mÃªs de MarÃ§o, o <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/demos/devderby\">Mozilla Dev Derby</a> tem como desafio desenvolver demos de CSS3 3D.<br>Pra quem nÃ£o conhece o Dev Derby, Ã© uma competiÃ§Ã£o promovida pela Mozilla para que desenvolvedores do mundo inteiro faÃ§am aplicaÃ§Ãµes com novas tecnologias.<br>JÃ¡ participei, fazendo um experimento com o History API do HTML5:<br><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/demos/detail/history-image-gallery\">https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/demos/detail/history-image-gallery</a>  </p>\n<p>Depois de assistir a <a href=\"http://felipenmoura.org/projects/lectures/css3-animation/#capa\">palestra</a> do <a href=\"http://twitter.com/felipenmoura\">@felipenmoura</a> e de ter umas aulas com ele sobre CSS3, resolvi fazer um pequeno experimento para submeter para o DevDerby.<br>O experimento Ã© um cubo 3D, totalmente feito com CSS3:<br><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/demos/detail/simple-css3-3d-cube\">https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/demos/detail/simple-css3-3d-cube</a>  </p>\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://developer.cdn.mozilla.net/media/uploads/demos/j/a/jaydson/2f34e7ff0d9f99c224333153519419cb/simple-css3-3d-cube_1330973828_demo_package/index.html\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://jaydson.org/wp-content/uploads/cube.jpg\"><img src=\"http://jaydson.org/wp-content/uploads/cube.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a>  </p>\n<p>Confiram lÃ¡, e se curtirem, cliquem no &quot;Like&quot; ;)</p>\n",
