        "title": "kactoos-api",
        "categories": ["Kactoos", "PHP"],
        "content": "<p>Para facilitar ainda mais a vida de quem quer desenvolver Apps utilizando a <a href=\"http://api.kactoos.com/docs\">API da Kactoos</a> criei uma biblioteca bem simples em PHP.\nA ideia Ã© abstrair todos os mÃ©todos existentes da API para serem consumidos em poucas linhas de codigo PHP.\nA lista de mÃ©todos Ã© essa:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>get-friends</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>get-product-categories</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>get-products-by-range-price</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>get-products-country</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>get-products-most-bought</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>get-product-list</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>get-my-favorites</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>get-my-groups</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>get-products-most-viewed</li>\n</ol>\n<p>O projeto estÃ¡ disponÃ­vel no Github: <a href=\"https://github.com/jaydson/Kactoos-API\">https://github.com/jaydson/Kactoos-API</a>\nA documentaÃ§Ã£o oficial da API\nAbaixo coloco alguns exemplos:</p>\n<p>[php]\n$kapi = new KactoosAPI();\n$kapi-&gt;oauthConsumerKey(&#39;[SEU_CONSUMER_KEY_AQUI]&#39;)\n -&gt;country(&#39;br&#39;)\n -&gt;module(&#39;products&#39;)\n -&gt;format(&#39;xml&#39;);</p>\n<p>/*</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sample code 1 - Get Product Categories with a specific name search\n*/\n$sample1 = $kapi-&gt;getProductCategories(&#39;categorie-name&#39;,&#39;android&#39;);\nprint_r($sample1);</li>\n</ul>\n<p>/*</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sample code 2 - Get Products by Range Price\n*/\n$sample2 = $kapi-&gt;getProductsByRange(900, 1100, &#39;best-price&#39;);\nprint_r($sample2);</li>\n</ul>\n<p>/*</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sample code 3 - Get Products most bought\n*/\n$sample3 = $kapi-&gt;getProductsMostBought(array(&#39;start&#39; =&gt; 3,\n&#39;orderby&#39; =&gt; &#39;date&#39;,\n&#39;limit&#39;=&gt;3));\nprint_r($sample3);</li>\n</ul>\n<p>[/php]</p>\n<p>Qualquer duvida, comentem. Qualquer Bug, consertem. :P</p>\n",
